review:
There are six (6) velvet headbands with buttons in this set. Each headband is narrow at only 8-3/4" wide and certainly not as wide as pictured on the Amazon site. Also, there are buttons on each side of the ear area. When I attach my mask to these buttons, my face mask is no longer tight to my face because the slinky velvet material moves and does not stay in place.

Overall, I do not like these at all. They will suffice as headbands only and not for mask attachment. The current price of $11.99 comes to $2 per band but I do not feel they are worth that price at all.

Product Title: Claw Hair Clips, IKOCO 6 Pack Jaw Clips Stylish Matte Plastic Strong Hold Hair Clamps Box Packaged for Thin Fine Hair with 10Pcs Black Hair ties (2.4Inch)
details: {"Brand": "IKOCO", "Hair Type": "Fine", "Color": "Green,Grey", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Material": "Plastic, Metal, Acrylic", "Product Dimensions": "6.25 x 4.25 x 2 inches; 5.89 Ounces"}
review:
This is a very nice set of 6 clips, 10 hair ties, and a case. The clips are strong and do hold a generous amount of hair. I like the non-slippery feeling of the clip itself. The ties are ordinary but still functional. The reason I rated this 3 stars is because I also ordered this same set with the blue clips and tan ties. One of the clips in that order broke immediately which tells me these won't last.

The current price of $7.19 is reasonable for this set but just be aware that the clips will break easily because the plastic is not that strong.

Product Title: JPNK 4PCS Anti-Static Detangling Fine & Wide Tooth Shower Comb Set
details: {"Material": "Plastic", "Brand": "JPNK", "Hair Type": "Wavy,Straight", "Unit Count": "1.00 Count", "Package Dimensions": "12 x 3.1 x 0.7 inches; 5.61 Ounces"}
review:
This is a nice set of combs--one wide-tooth and one sort of fine-tooth with two regularly-spaced ones. I know others mentioned that they found the combs to be sharp on the edges when combing. The one wide-tooth comb has blunted tines but the other three have pointed tines. However, those pointed tine ones were not sharp on my scalp. I have short to medium fine curly hair and these passed through my hair easily (wet or dry) and I did not feel scratched. I actually like the points massaging my scalp because on the combs I received, they were not super sharp.

Unfortunately, I cannot tell if this set is wooden as it claims. It is possible they are wooden but because they are highly polished, they feel and look like plastic. I attend craft shows and it is possible to get a plastic feel and look to wood, so unless I broke one of the combs in half (which I am unwilling to do), I cannot tell. I still think the current price of $9.99 is reasonable even they are plastic.

Product Title: Organic Sweet Almond Oil and Fractionated Coconut Oil Bundle for Hair and Skin, 100% Pure and Natural, Hexane-Free, Moisturizing, For Healthy Skin, Silky Hair, Multiuse Body Oil, 16 fl. Oz X 2
details: {"Brand": "Shiny Leaf", "Scent": "Almond Oil and Fractionated Coconut", "Item Form": "Oil", "Unit Count": "32.00 Fl Oz", "Number of Items": "2", "Package Dimensions": "8.62 x 5.04 x 2.48 inches; 2.23 Pounds", "UPC": "781584950669"}
review:
I am finding SO many uses for Shiny Leaf's coconut and sweet almond oil! I do have some experience with coconut oil but this is my first time using sweet almond oil. Thanks the labels on the bottles, reviews and internet searches, I'm finding SO many ways to use these oils...sometimes together, sometimes individually.

Because I have terribly dry, sensitive skin, my main goal was to see how one or both oils could help protect my skin, especially now that winter has arrived and my skin is REALLY taking a beating. Both oils work well to hydrate and moisturize, so I mixed a few ounces of each in a mist bottle. After I bathe, I mist a combo of the oils over my skin to help hydrate and moisturize. The oils absorb quickly and do not leave an oily/greasy look OR feel to my skin. I'm already seeing a decrease in my dry skin/itchy red patches of skin. I experience NO discomfort whatsoever when misting these oils onto my sensitive skin. Both oils also work wonders on hair by moisturizing, hydrating, improving hair texture/strength, stimulate hair growth /thicken hair, and nourish the scalp to prevent dry, itchy flakes. In addition to using my combo of oils after bathing, I also give my hair a spray or two with the mister and sure enough, I'm seeing less hair in the drain and on my hairbrush after brushing. My hair is soft, smooth and shiny WITHOUT looking or feeling oily/greasy from the oil combo.

I use the coconut oil (alone) to help remove makeup, under and around my eyes to soften and reduce fine lines, I rub a small amount into my scalp (as does my husband) to help stimulate hair growth, on the kid's faces after their baths to soften (especially in cold weather!), on my nail beds every couple of days and a light amount on any patches of eczema/red skin. (It relieves the itching/burning and redness from eczema quickly!)

I use the sweet almond oil (alone) on dark circles under my eyes, a SMALL amount on split ends in my hair, a drop on chapped lips, I'm just starting to tinker with it for aromatherapy purposes. I recently learned that it can help fade scars so I've begun to rub some sweet almond oil into a scar on my finger to see what happens. If it helps, I'll then move on to a small facial scar I have. I'm also trying something on my own; just started doing this a few days ago. I get nosebleeds every single day, at least once a day, throughout the winter when the heat is on in the house. This started when I was 2 years old, I'm now 49 so I've experienced this my entire life. I now rub a small amount of sweet almond oil under my nostrils before bed. Since starting this, I continue to have nosebleeds. Yesterday, I had only one and it involved just a few drops of blood. I didn't whip through numerous tissues like normal. ONE tissue took care of it. (that's huge for me!) I have NO clue if its just a coincidence or if the sweet almond oil is helping in any way but I'm going to continue using it.

These oils are phenomenal! Both bottles are 16oz. I love the fact that they have normal caps on them but pumps for each bottle are included as well. The liquid of each is thinner oil than I expected, which I prefer. Both absorb quickly. Neither has a scent. I've found SO many uses for these oils, I can't wait to discover more. ( I'm SO happy with these oils, I recently purchased Shiny Leaf's biotin hair conditioner and cannot wait to try it! ) I find the price to be incredibly reasonable, especially since you're getting TWO bottles of oils! HIGHLY recommended!

*FYI...the mist bottle on the end in my photo is NOT included! I used one of my own mist bottles to combine both oils. You will get both bottles AND pumps that you see in my photo, NOT the mist sprayer!

details: {"Brand": "SMPL objects", "Material": "Polyester", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Pattern": "Marble", "Number of Items": "1", "Package Dimensions": "9.21 x 6.97 x 0.67 inches; 0.63 Ounces", "Manufacturer": "SMPL Objects", "Country of Origin": "China"}
review:
An adorable shower cap that fits my large head. It says it fits up to 24" head, and mine measures 23.5". Then I have loads of hair- semi thick, nearly waist length. It all fits! Yet isn't a big bulbous excess of material either. But I am definitely pushing max space available (again, I have a large head).

I simply dont wash my hair every day, but I do hop in the shower. I dont notice my hair getting wet at all, but I dont put my head in the water even with this on. I have a spray nozzle for washing and rinsing, so I guess I am able to control where the water reaches better.

The fit is surprisingly good. The rear has an elastic portion to provide a nice fit. The spacing left over once in place is reasonable for my large head and mane of hair. I really was skeptical, but am glad I went ahead and got this. I have some cute shower caps, but none as nice as this. The little bow on top makes me feel like I went back in time to the 50s or something. Adorbs!

I dont use it for keeping my hair out of face for make up or skin care, but it would certainly do well for that too. Also, if I had pool.. while it isnt a pool cap, if I just wanted something to help keep excess water off my hair while casually wading in a pool, this very well could work for that too.

details: {"Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Product Dimensions": "30.71 x 3.35 x 9.06 inches; 8.78 Ounces"}
review:
This Havtyyise-3 set is nice. I really like the hand mitt. The holes on each side are better than the ones with no holes. This made it easier to get the soap on and keep the mitt on all at the same time.

The set comes with a mitt, a handled back scrubber, and a pouf ball. The mitt is the best in the back and the back scrubber comes in second. I do not like the way the pouf ball is made and I don't see it lasting very long. It just flattens out because it is poorly made.

I will be recommending this Havtyyise-3 set to family and friends but I will let everybody know about the pouf ball.

review:
This is a nice intimate wash for women. It is free of alcohol, sulfate and parabens which is great since you don't want those ingredients in there. It is also vegan and plant based which is great. It produces a nice gentle lather that works well and I found I don't need much when I use it. They made sure that it maintains the natural pH of the skin so you are not prone to infections.

The fragrance is ok in my eyes and it works well overall. The price is a bit on the more expensive side considering how much product you get, however considering that it is vegan and all, I think it kind of makes up for it. I am not upset with this product and mine was not expired yet but close, but these types of products can be used at least 3 years past that date so I have no issues with that as well.

Product Title: Claw Hair Clips, IKOCO 6 Pack Jaw Clips Stylish Matte Plastic Strong Hold Hair Clamps Box Packaged for Thin Fine Hair with 10Pcs Black Hair ties (2.4Inch)
details: {"Brand": "IKOCO", "Hair Type": "Fine", "Color": "Green,Grey", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Material": "Plastic, Metal, Acrylic", "Product Dimensions": "6.25 x 4.25 x 2 inches; 5.89 Ounces"}
review: In this pack for just over $7 you get 3 different colored hair clips and 2 each color, and then 7 hair ties. The hair clips are gold, silver and black and just beautiful. The hair ties are a plain black. These hair clips are a different, new design and  I wasn’t sure if they would work for my hair, but fear not they did. I have long, but thin hair, thin in density and thin in thickness and this hair clip worked just fine. I had no issues gathering just a section or the entire hair together. Even though the clips are flat in the front I had no issues at all working with these, they are actually quite easy to work with and fit quite comfortably in the hair. The size is big enough to fit my entire hair or just parts of it. They are cute and lovely and the price is not excessive, they are actually inexpensive if you ask me.

Product Title: Organic Sweet Almond Oil and Fractionated Coconut Oil Bundle for Hair and Skin, 100% Pure and Natural, Hexane-Free, Moisturizing, For Healthy Skin, Silky Hair, Multiuse Body Oil, 16 fl. Oz X 2
details: {"Brand": "Shiny Leaf", "Scent": "Almond Oil and Fractionated Coconut", "Item Form": "Oil", "Unit Count": "32.00 Fl Oz", "Number of Items": "2", "Package Dimensions": "8.62 x 5.04 x 2.48 inches; 2.23 Pounds", "UPC": "781584950669"}
review:
You get 2 massive bottles of oil, one with sweet almond oil and the other with coconut oil. For each bottle they supply you with a pump dispenser which is great. It makes it so much easier to dispense the oil without making a mess to be honest. Both oils are claimed to be organic which is nice. This will run you $25 which in my eyes is a good deal.

These oils can be used direct for skin care and as carrier oils, meaning you can add some essential oils to them to make your own custom oil blends. The oils themselves were pretty much fragrance-free which was a bit disappointing to me, but makes sense since these are often used as carrier oils. When you use this they are pretty lightweight and absorb quickly. I found they do leave the skin a bit greasy, but that is not a surprise since these are oils. That feeling does go away within about 15 minutes or so, so not too bad. All in all a good deal

review:
Body butter is the perfect after-bath treat for your skin. Zia body butter is a combination of shea butter and mango butter blended into a smooth moisturizer that could become a hand cream essential. (The small sample container in the Spa To Go kits fits nicely in your purse.)

This cream is super luxurious to use in the winter. This is one of the few products with myrrh essential oil.

Ingredients: Infusion of organic aloe vera extract, organic ginko biloba extract, organic elder extract, organic chamomile extract, caprylic/capric triglyceride, stearic acid, glycerin, glyceryl stearate, safflower oil, shea butter, mango butter, polysorbate 60, stearyl alcohol, sweet almond oil, tocopherol, beta carotene, rosehip seed oil, cucumber extract, green tea extract, algae extract, sodium carbomer, lavender essential oil, myrrh essential oil, neroli essential oil, vetiver essential oil, benzoin gum, phenoxyethanol, methylparaben, propylparaben.

Zia body butter is a rich moisturizing cream that absorbs fast and leaves your skin looking smooth and deeply moisturized. Using this product after the brown sugar body buff and Lavender Clary Sage Body Wash takes smooth skin to entirely new levels. If you use these three products and take a salt bath, then you may reach spa nirvana.

~The Rebecca Review

Product Title: TULA Probiotic Skin Care Supersize 24-7 Moisture Hydrating Day & Night Cream | Holiday 2020, Ageless is the New Anti-Aging, Face Cream, Contains Watermelon Fruit and Blueberry Extract | 3.4 oz
details: {"Brand": "TULA", "Scent": "Watermelon", "Item Form": "Cream", "Unit Count": "3.4 Ounce", "Number of Items": "1", "Package Dimensions": "5.43 x 5.16 x 3.43 inches; 3.4 Ounces", "UPC": "850014698355"}
review:
Although I'm not thrilled that this didn't have a safety seal on it, the cream itself is very good. It's a heavy cream, despite the company identifying it as being light and whipped. It looks whipped in the jar, but it is not light on the face. I don't think it would be suitable for all ages. Because of the heaviness and intense moisturizing, I believe that mature skin is going to benefit most from using this.
For reference, I'm in my early 60s, in a dry climate, with combination skin (T Zone) and some wrinkles as a point of concern.
This cream works very well with all of the above. I don't put it on my nose, of course, but when I feel like a splurge I put it on my hands because it's so moisturizing.
The claim that it moisturizes 24/7 is indeed true. Even in this dry area, my face feels hydrated all day when I use this cream.
It contains milk protein, yogurt extract, blueberry extract, rice protein, and a host of other skin-loving ingredients.

I hope this review has helped you to make a decision about whether or not you'd like to invest in this product. It is indeed generously sized at 3.4 oz, and it has a very high quality ingredients. But like I said, it's not going to be for everyone.

xxoo

review:
We have been having such fun since receiving this wig! My daughter has long, dark blond hair, but she wanted to go out one night looking like a character from her favorite TV show. We received the light blonde wig and in minutes, she had long, white-blonde hair that was straight on top and had curls towards the bottom! This wig’s construction is terrific, and it is adjustable.
This wig It is made of pretty soft fibers, and you can run your hands over the hair, brush it gently and feel the softness, It has a top tie- on to secure the wig, and the cap lets your scalp breathe. Since it is a rally long haired wig, it is not going to be lightweight: but it doesn’t feel heavy on your head. The color is a white/blonde like just like the TV character and the braids on top can be kept, re-braided or let loose to change the style. And although I was able to purchase this wig at a big discount in exchange for my honest review (and my stars cannot be bought, folks, this is truly my unbiased and honest opinion), I think these prices are completely reasonable and I will be buying more for events where my daughter or I need a different look. Go ahead and try this company’s wigs! Have fun with it! We are!

Product Title: Organic Sweet Almond Oil and Fractionated Coconut Oil Bundle for Hair and Skin, 100% Pure and Natural, Hexane-Free, Moisturizing, For Healthy Skin, Silky Hair, Multiuse Body Oil, 16 fl. Oz X 2
details: {"Brand": "Shiny Leaf", "Scent": "Almond Oil and Fractionated Coconut", "Item Form": "Oil", "Unit Count": "32.00 Fl Oz", "Number of Items": "2", "Package Dimensions": "8.62 x 5.04 x 2.48 inches; 2.23 Pounds", "UPC": "781584950669"}
review:
First, I will say these oils seem fine. They work well together or apart, mixed into other skincare products or alone. I use these types of oils to make my own facial oil mix or to add to my moisturizer.
The thing I absolutely hate that companies do to try to sell their products is to say things that aren't true. The USDA does not certify oils - food, cosmetic, or otherwise. The fact that the bottle says this product is USDA certified on one side, and the other side says not intended for ingestion should speak volumes. The USDA certifies and regulates the welfare and production of food products; meaning products that you ingest. So, why on earth would they certify a product you cannot ingest? The bottle also makes outright claims of known cures from using these oils. There is no disclaimer on either bottle that states that these claims have not been approved or proven by the FDA, or whatever the disclaimer is that is mandatory. There are ingredients listed, one ingredient for each product, the oil, and that's it. Nothing tells how these oils were extracted. Therefore, we do not know if they are refined or unrefined. They probably don't know either. So you see, therein lies the lies and deception.
These oils would be much better if they weren't tied to lies. Because you know what they say about lies... if you tell one you have to tell more to keep up with the first one. Is what they say in the bottle really what's in the bottle? Are they pure oils or mixed with a lesser oil? Oils are greasy. If they are unrefined, why aren't they greasy? When you refine oils, you take away a lot of their natural properties and their nutritive value, is that why they aren't greasy? Because of the lies and lack of important information, I really don't know for sure what these oils are.
Because of the deceptive practices and claims made, I would not recommend these or any of their other oils.

Product Title: Benton Aloe Propolis Soothing Gel & Benton Cleansing Foam with 2 Benton Masks ( Bundle )
details: {"Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Package Dimensions": "6.85 x 3.94 x 2.2 inches; 11.22 Ounces", "UPC": "608119365302"}
review: This kit is a great deal!  I've been a devoted user of Korean skin care products.  For a while, I have preferred, out of several brands and types of sheet mask, the Benton Bee and Snail sheet mask.  Fantastic product!!!!  Firms, smooths, soothes.  It's great.  However, that's not why I purchased this set.  I have combo skin that leans towards oily in the heat.  Super oily T-zone.  After doing a ton of research, I decided to give the Benton Aloe Gel moisturizer a try.  I'd also heard great things about this foam cleanser.  I'm really enjoying the cleanser so far.  I wet my hands and face, use only a pea sized amount, rub my hands together to create the foam (not a soapy lather, but a thick and creamy foam), and work over my face.  I do this after oil cleansing.  This does a great job of picking up any oil residue and dirt, while leaving my face soft and refreshed.  Never tight and dry, which is the sign of an awful cleanser.  The gel moisturizer is okay.  Just okay.  I don't get as oily as I did with lotion moisturizers, which is great.  However, I don't have that supple, smooth feel that I'm used to and prefer.  I've actually noticed flaking around my nose, which is something I never dealt with after moisturizing.  A pea sized amount covers my entire face, it leaves a slightly tacky finish until absorbed ( I always let each of my products absorb for around 90 seconds before applying the next step), and is completely colorless.  Will I repurchase?  No, but I do suggest that you give this a try if your research and needs point you this direction.  Everyone's skin care needs can vary on several levels.  There are universal musts for good skin health, like cleansing daily, moisturizing, and using a good sunscreen.  There a a ton a variations of those products, though.  Finding the right routine and products can be a trial and error process.  The main thing is to stick to it.  The results are worth it!

features: ['Perfect for a large makeup collection', 'Built-in 14 brush holder in lid with cover; Customize space with 5 adjustable dividers', 'Convenient handle for easy carrying; Sturdy key lock', 'Removable, divided, upper tray for simple access to lower compartment', 'Hard-sided construction prevents items from being crushed']
details: {"Product Dimensions": "9.75 x 9.13 x 15.38 inches; 2.8 Pounds", "Item model number": "VZ03755", "UPC": "826030037553", "Manufacturer": "Ideastream Consumer Products, LLC"}
review:
Originally I left a bad review about it not locking, but I realized soon after that I just wasn't turning the key far enough because I thought the resistance I was meeting was the end of the lock turn.

After trying a few times I realize now it was my error in assuming the item was faulty and I am now correcting my review to rate it properly.

The Case is sturdy with a decent lock on it. I do wish it was a slightly different design as the lock although it does in fact lock it seems weak and anyone with any time on their hands could easily snap it probably with just a butter knife. Which I hope doesn't happen as I bought this item specifically to protect my make up from the greedy grubby hands of my own family since I had high end make up stolen from my current non locking case.

I do recommend this item for light protection of products and belongings but nothing more than that.

Cute design is definitely a selling feature.

Please measure and confirm your hair dryer nozzle diameter BEFORE purchase.', 'FITS XTAVA BLACK ORCHID HAIR DIFFUSER: SnozzlePro’s super-tight fit on the Xtava Black Orchid Hair Diffuser is designed to grip and support the added weight of this short nozzle hair diffuser.', "PREVENTS CONCENTRATOR NOZZLE POP-OFFS: SnozzlePro's patented design keeps hair dryer concentrator nozzles securely attached for a perfect fit and protects hands from heat.", 'HOW TO USE - SnozzlePro comes with detailed HOW-TO-USE instructions. details: {"Product Dimensions": "2.5 x 2.5 x 2.5 inches; 2.08 Ounces", "Item model number": "SP-100", "UPC": "860002276502", "Manufacturer": "Snozzle Pro"}
review:
This wonderful product allowed me to continue using my favorite T3 Featherweight blowdryer with my new Xtava Black Orchid diffuser!! I didn't have to buy a new blowdryer! I will admit that I measured the wrong thing when I ordered the SnozzlePro adapter (I measured the base of the concentrator nozzle that came with the blowdryer and not the actual blowdryer nozzle - oops!) My blowdryer is actually a little wider than the measurements given for the SnozzlePro. It was so close, I was determined to make it work! I was able to do it with a little manipulation and a slender tool to give just a little extra stretch to get the SnozzlePro over the end of the blowdryer nozzle (used a tool WITHOUT any sharp edges or points, nothing that could damage the SnozzlePro or the blowdryer). **I did this at my own risk - knowing that I could possibly damage the SnozzlePro or my blowdryer!!** Very gently, I was able to get the SnozzlePro onto my blowdryer. I made sure it was evenly attached all the way around before adding the Xtava Black Orchid diffuser. I attached the diffuser to the SnozzlePro AFTER I put the SnozzlePro on the blowdryer - the opposite of what the instructions advise you to do. (also note that before attaching the SnozzlePro to the blowdryer, I put the diffuser on the SnozzlePro a couple of times to make sure it fit properly and that I would be able to attach it without needing to use the other end of the adapter to make sure it was secure). After getting everything in place, I'm happy to say that it's very secure and there's nothing that is loose or has any wiggle room whatsoever!! I'm never removing it!! It's there until the dryer kicks the bucket or something breaks! It's working beautifully! It holds very tightly and securely, it hasn't slipped or moved at all since I attached everything!! You can see in the pics how tightly it's holding. I love drying my hair with this diffuser! My hair looks amazing and dries faster than when I used to use a round brush! No more work drying with a round brush! Just using this diffuser and moving it to different sections of my hair, it's easier than ever to dry my hair! Thank you for making this product that allows us to use this wonderful diffuser on other brands of blowdryers! I will be recommending it to everyone who has curly hair!

Update - the adapter and diffuser has come off a couple of times and it takes a little bit of work to get it back on because my blow dryer is a tiny bit bigger than the measurements but I can get it back on. I think it came off because I accidentally held it by the adapter or grabbed it by the diffuser. Definitely only hold it by the barrel of the blow dryer (like in my 3rd pic) or the handle for the blow dryer!

details: {"Brand": "SMPL objects", "Material": "Polyester", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Pattern": "Marble", "Number of Items": "1", "Package Dimensions": "9.21 x 6.97 x 0.67 inches; 0.63 Ounces", "Manufacturer": "SMPL Objects", "Country of Origin": "China"}
review:
I usually get packs of cheapola showercaps from the dollar store (like a six pack of plastic bags with a rubberband, you know?) but they don't last long... So I had a vinyl one that lasted longer, but was really just that same old design that was just plastic tied to your head with elastic...

This shower cap is... well, frankly, after the other ones I've used... luxurious. The material is not plastic, but more like the soft nylon on my windbreaker jacket. It's much quieter when I'm in the shower, which makes for a more peaceful bathing experience. It is also more comfortable, as the headband is more fitted. It's especially comfortable if you wear it over your ears... there's no pressure anywhere, but it still keeps your hair dry. I, personally, like to have my ears "out," so there is some pressure to the top of my ears where the headband sits, but I don't mind it.

The headband does stretch a bit for head size, but not as much as you might be used to if you've used shower caps with elastic bands. I kind of liked this... It makes it easier to get all my hair in it. I flip my head upside down over the shower cap, and the cap just kind of catches my hair like a bucket, and I can just tuck in any stragglers before flipping my head back up. If you need to tighten the headband just a little bit, you can re-tie the bow for a slight adjustment.

No shower cap is going to be completely, perfectly water tight. You're always going to get a little bit of water around the edges unless you're really careful in the shower and take pains to avoid direct spray. I use a shower cap when I take a shower before bed and don't want to go to sleep with wet hair... a little bit of moisture doesn't bother me, as I'm not trying to protect a hairstyle or anything. I really just like the comfort and feel of this cap a lot!

Product Title: stila Perfect Me, Perfect Hue Eye & Cheek Palette, Fair/Light
details: {"Color": "Fair/Light", "Brand": "stila", "Item Form": "Powder", "Special Feature": "Curated to work with your skin tone, but each palette is wearable on all skin tones.", "Product Benefits": "Curated to work with your skin tone, but each palette is wearable on all skin tones.", "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Product Dimensions": "3.62 x 0.59 x 3.7 inches; 4.48 Ounces", "Item model number": "SB80010001", "UPC": "094800351073", "Manufacturer": "stila"}
review:
I purchased this product in a store, but I am such a fan I had to write a review. Ever since I purchased this palette, it has been my go-to for everyday makeup. I am fair-skinned with dark hair and hazel eyes, and the colors are perfect. I don't always use every color in a palette and I don't always place the colors as directed, but in this case, Stila knows what they are talking about!

The large color on the left is your all-over base, and I apply that first. Next, I go to the top right corner and apply this grayish color from crease to browbone. Third, I take the darkest color and place it quite heavily (but narrowly) in the crease and a little in the corner and lash line. Next, I put the highlight (lightest) color just under the brow and also outside the inner corner of the eye. Finally, I put the shimmery gold-like color in the middle across the lid and blend all the colors with a blending brush. I use the darker blush normally, but use the light one as a highlight if I want the added effect. I love that when I am doing my makeup on the run, I only have to grab this one container and my makeup brushes (I have the EcoTools Eye Enhancing Duo Brush set with four tips on two brushes, so even there you don't have to take as much with you).

The quality of the product is excellent and it blends well. Other than the darkest brown, the eyeshadow pigments are not super intense, so you can go light or apply more for a deeper intensity.

This cap is very comfortable, I like the pattern (it's not immediately apparent that it's shower-related) and it looks very well made: over-locked edges, a not-slip trip along the forehead and a sassy bow on the side. The fabric is velvety-soft on the outside, very pleasing to the touch, and waterproof on the inside, but it does not make any crunchy/rubbery noise like an old raincoat. I'm very pleased with my purchase, and this looks like it can be a very nice self-care gift for others.

details: {"Brand": "Karma Cosmetics", "Item Form": "Gel", "Skin Type": "Dry", "Material Feature": "Natural", "Recommended Uses For Product": "Exfoliating,Moisturize,Calluses", "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Product Dimensions": "8 x 1.5 x 6 inches; 5.61 Ounces", "Item model number": "footmask1", "UPC": "782150609615"}
review:
UPDATE AS OF 03/16/2019 All the previous info still applies. Now that I am 16 days out from using this product, I want to add that my feet are STILL peeling. I have been using this type (not this particular) product for a couple of years and the entire process is always completed at least by day 12. Thus, besides the horrible odor, this product is not particularly efficient at exfoliating. So, basically there is NOTHING about it that I can recommend.

No matter how good these are at exfoliating, I cannot recommend them due to the offensive/clingy/cloying/LONGLASTING odor. I have used products like this before and there is always some odor during use...but these, well, days later after soaking my feet in baking soda water and then vinegar water, the incredibly floral+chemical odor still wafts around my head--yes, all the way from my feet! It is sickening, offensive,, and embarrassing when I am around other people. Also, the socks I put on after using this product have been washed in hot water and laundry detergent and they are just going to have to be thrown away because the odor DOES NOT come out. I threw away second set of these bootees because I cannot subject myself to the odor again no matter how badly I want my feet to be soft without rough skin. DO NOT BUY if you are sensitive to odors and/or simply do not like strong odors wafting around you for days on end.

features: ['HIGH QUALITY NEW -Handmade 6.0"Long good for Barber/Salon use or home', 'ERGONOMIC HANDLE MOLDED FINGER REST -for smooth easyCutting less stress on hands and back', 'JAPANESE STEEL-handmade hollow ground convex Sharp edges for long lasting sharpness', 'FREE -LEATHER CASE -zips up great for traveling', '-100% SATISFACTION GUARANTEE!-your satisfaction is important to Mosher Salon Tools']
details: {"Material": "Leather", "Brand": "Mosher Salon Tools", "Blade Material": "Stainless Steel", "Item Dimensions LxWxH": "8.19 x 4.02 x 0.98 inches", "Style": "Japanese", "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Product Dimensions": "8.19 x 4.02 x 0.98 inches; 0.8 Ounces", "Item model number": "M60", "UPC": "641938982688", "Manufacturer": "Mosher Salon Tools"}
review:
I learned some things when I was looking for hair cutting shears. Mostly that you can pay around $200 for the best ones,used by professionals,and,that you need very sharp scissors or shears to cut or trim hair.

I've been trimming and shaping my own hair for a long time and am usually happy with the results,considering too many times,when I would go to a salon to have it cut or shaped or trimmed,they did a job I was almost always disappointed with. I decided a long time ago,if someone was going to screw up my hair,it might as well be me. At least I have a good idea on when to stop cutting it and I actually care what the final result looks like.

I also have fine,wavy hair. Not the easiest to cut.

I have noticed,and maybe it was from using whatever scissors were around at the time,that sometimes the ends do look a bit frazzled;and in researching shears,I found out that unless the blades are very sharp,the ends can break,or result in split ends. I don't have split ends and never noticed them,except for a long,long time ago when I was a teenager;but,I have used these once to do some light trimming and shaping;with wavy hair you are always shaping,cutting with the wave and not cutting against the wave. And,these shears have produced a nice result. And I don't see the somewhat frazzled or lightningbolt effect at the ends of my hair,that I sometimes get.

I've used these just once,I only trim my hair to maintain healthy looking ends,and I did it a few weeks ago,and I like these and I'm glad I looked for something better than "any old scissors" that I have on hand.

review: Prior to discovering this product, I used another, much pricier coverup.  It was ok but the applicator was strange and a lot of the expensive cream was wasted.  Also, it didn't last all day.  Pur concealer is perfect.  It spreads easily, blends in nicely and does the job.  Even my undereye dark circles are minimized.  It looks like a small amount of product but a little goes a long way and the tube lasts a very long time, even with daily use.  Update 4/15/2022:  Many months ago, I purchased a second tube of this product because I figured the first tube would soon be gone.  Not so!  Here it is, at least 4 months later and, even with generous daily use, it's only this morning I had to open the new tube.  Great product, lasts a long time, easy to apply and well priced.  The folks who don't like the applicator might try dapping on the small amount needed and spreading it with a fingertip.  Works great that way.

Product Title: Philips Norelco T970 Accu-Vac Beard and Moustache Trimmer
features: ['Stainless Steel Self Sharpening Blades offer lifetime precision cutting', 'Patented zoom lock locks into 9 different settings for your desired beard length', 'Rechargeable, Cord / Cordless for use with our without a cord.', '1 hour charge time, battery level indicator', '60 Day Money Back Guarantee']
details: {"Package Dimensions": "9.7 x 6 x 4.6 inches; 1.58 Pounds", "Item model number": "T970", "UPC": "075020189707", "Manufacturer": "Philips Norelco"}
review:
When my (non-vacuuming) Norelco trimmer would no longer take a charge, I ordered this item, not too concerned over whether the vacuum was effective or not.

What I received was a poorly designed trimmer:

1. To hold the trimmer, one must place one's hands over the vacuum air exit slots, thus throttling the vacuum.

2. The guard was so complex to attach and detach that it took 10 minutes each time to do it.

3. The closeness settings don't actually lock in, and tend to "wander" toward (1), the closest setting. And so I would find myself completing my trim with 3/4" length hair on one side of my face, graduating to stubble on the other.

I finally threw the thing in the garbage after a week and bought a leftover non-vacuum Norelco model like the one I previously had - $19.99.

So, if you see some poor soul walking down the street with long whiskers on one side of his face, and a 5 o'clock shadow on the other, be kind. He's probably not dimented - just the victim of this "new and improved" beard trimmer.

review:
People are likely reacting to the lavender.
It doesn't make it a bad product, so if you've had a reaction, stop using it. But it doesn't mean everyone is going to have a reaction.
Most people's eyes will sting. Lavender in the eye really sucks.
Micellular water in the eye does too.
Micellular Water and lavender in the eye is really painful. I recommend using a Q tip to remove eye makeup.
I have used micellular water in other brands.
This does an ok job. It's very comparable.
But I'm sensitive to the lavender, which sucks because I love the calming scent.
The pump is a nice touch.. But it's on the cheap side. If you shake the bottle, it will spill out from the pump if you don't cover that hole.
If I wasn't sensitive to the lavender, it'd be worth purchasing again.

Product Title: Philips Norelco T970 Accu-Vac Beard and Moustache Trimmer
features: ['Stainless Steel Self Sharpening Blades offer lifetime precision cutting', 'Patented zoom lock locks into 9 different settings for your desired beard length', 'Rechargeable, Cord / Cordless for use with our without a cord.', '1 hour charge time, battery level indicator', '60 Day Money Back Guarantee']
details: {"Package Dimensions": "9.7 x 6 x 4.6 inches; 1.58 Pounds", "Item model number": "T970", "UPC": "075020189707", "Manufacturer": "Philips Norelco"}
review:
I understand that there are differing opinions on this trimmer, but after using it back to back with the Remington Precision Pro MB-400 Titanium Vaccuum Mustache and Beard Trimmer, there is no comparison on the following counts:

1) quality of the trimming accessories - the Norelco has a flimsy cutting guide, and its all on the verge of breaking everytime you use it. Anyone who has had a previous Norelco product points this out.

2) a ridiculously designed sideburn trimmer - It is so hard to get the trimmer set-up! a poor design

3) A terrible cut - if you have even a medium beard, the trimmer is very uneven. you can certainly do better.

The items above are enough to walk away from this device. The reviews that critique the vaccuum are probably being unrealistic. It is in part Norelco's fault - they set you up to expect more from the vaccuum than you get. But simple physics will tell you it is going to miss a lot of hair.

It was such a bad experience, I had to review it.

Product Title: Empty Brown Glass Spray Bottles2-Pack, Refillable 16 oz Containers for Essential Oils, Cleaning Products, Aromatherapy, Misting Plants, or Cooking - Reliable Sprayer with Mist and Stream Settings
details: {"Brand": "Cherry", "Material": "Glass", "Capacity": "16 Ounces", "Number of Items": "2", "Product Care Instructions": "Hand Wash Only", "Package Dimensions": "9.09 x 6.46 x 3.35 inches; 4.94 Ounces", "UPC": "791523234187"}
review:
This is the second set of spray bottles of this type that I have ordered. Each set has been from a different brand/seller. They both perform exactly the same. I use them to make my own household cleaners, room sprays, toilet sprays, etc. I'm not a fan of our cultures plastic addiction & try to reduce my impact on the planet when I can. Running my own eco family farm full time helps considerably ;)

I like everything about these bottles except for the same exact thing I don't like about my other set of bottles, the spray head rotates easily. It doesn't unscrew, that's not what I'm talking about. It's the spray head itself. I think if the bottle wasn't so heavy this wouldn't be an issue, but when spraying downward, the bottle will move due to the weight. If I hold the bottle with one hand, while spraying with the other, all is well.

A possible solution to this might be to purchase these 16 oz amber glass bottles separately, then purchase a separate pack of very highly rated, top quality spray nozzles & a sheet of labels to see if that helps. Perhaps these sets are being sold with lower quality spray nozzles. I really cannot say. I currently don't have a need to order a bunch of bottles in this size & enjoy the convenience of having a ready made kit of 2, so for now, I'm happy enough with what I have.

details: {"Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Item model number": "Crema Tepezcohuite"}
review:
I've used tepezcohuite for years and purchased creams and ointments in Mexico with truly amazing medicinal properties, but I was absolutely disappointed with this product. It is clearly a petroleum base that smells and has the texture of machinery grease. It doesn't have the color of the real bark, and since there are no ingredients listed, my guess is, it's petroleum jelly with some coloring. I'm surprised Amazon sells it without any information at all.

The positive reviews are either fake or people don't realize that if you put any type of oil or grease on your skin it will keep the moisture in. But this product will never do what real tepezcohuite can. I'd never put this grease on my skin, so it was a complete waste of money.

details: {"Brand": "Shiny Leaf", "Scent": "Almond Oil and Fractionated Coconut", "Item Form": "Oil", "Unit Count": "32.00 Fl Oz", "Number of Items": "2", "Package Dimensions": "8.62 x 5.04 x 2.48 inches; 2.23 Pounds", "UPC": "781584950669"}
review:
My oils arrived in bottles with security seals beneath the lids. Each bottle has a cap but a pump accompanies each bottle as well. I much prefer the pumps for oils since they are thinner and it can be difficult to control a pour. During the winter months I use these oils as skin moisturizers. When still damp from a shower, I rub the oil on my skin and it moisturizes much better than any type of lotion that I have tried.

These oils also make wonderful body scrubs using essential oils for scent and sugar or salt for the exfoliating. Using the scrubs also helps to moisturize.

I found the oils to be fresh, no sign of a rancid smell. They both come in an amber colored bottle which is the best way to store them.

Just in case you are not familiar with these types of oils, they are not scented. Neither oil has any type of scent at all and they are meant to be used as moisturizing products or carrier oils.

Overall: really nice set of oils that are fresh and in the right type of bottle.

review:
I thought I had cleaned my face well when I used a cleanser, but apparently not. This Micellar Water removed so much dirt and oil that I can't believe I thought my skin was cleaned before using it. I didn't use it to remove makeup only to clean my skin.

It left my skin soft and smelled good. I love the natural ingredients. I love that you don't have to rinse it. It's hard to find a toner that has ingredients that are not harmful to your skin and this is one that fits that description.

I am very pleased.

I have sensitive skin and it didn't burn or irritate my skin. I also have very dry skin and it didn't dry my face or neck out.

review: I have heard about how wonderful this DHC Deep Cleansing Oil is for a long time, but was put off by the price for what seems to be a bottle of olive oil with a pump.  I really like the way my face feels after cleansing with DHC.  Soft and smooth, and very clean.  When I finish cleansing, I wipe my face with a cotton pad and Micellar water.  After using this oil, the pad is perfectly clean, not a trace of the makeup I removed.  Other products were not this thorough.  I am still not convinced I am getting more than a bottle of olive oil, but I am very pleased with the performance of this product.

Product Title: Greenwich Bay Trading Company Fall & Winter Soap Sampler 15 pack of 1.9oz bars - Bundle 15 items
features: ['French-milled, luxurious vegetable soaps enriched with shea butter, essential oils and natural extracts in captivating botanical scents.', 'Paper-wrapped and offered in a 1.9oz mini soap square. Each Soap measures 2"x2"x1"', 'Great Fall and Winter Fragrances. Perfect for the holiday season.', 'Poly bagged and ready for your packaging.', 'Top Quality Soaps Made right here in the USA']
details: {"Item Form": "Bar", "Brand": "Greenwich Bay Trading Company Soaps", "Scent": "Eucalyptus, Honey, Pear, Peppermint, Chocolate, Ginger, Lily, Cranberry", "Material Feature": "Organic, Natural", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Product Dimensions": "8 x 4 x 6 inches; 2.05 Pounds", "UPC": "637776998424 794168192348", "Manufacturer": "Greenwich Bay Trading Company Soaps"}
review:
I ordered the 15 piece set of 1.9oz bars in the fall/winter scents. What I received was exactly as described. The soaps are so fragrant that I could smell them the second I opened the shipping box. The blend of multiple scents was a little bit overwhelming, but individually, these are incredible!

I can't pick a single favorite because they all smell so rich and lovely, but I'm rather partial to the Spiced Pumpkin, which I'm currently using in my bathroom. The whole room smells like pumpkin and cinnamon when I lather up, like I said these are super fragrant. The soap itself lathers nicely and has just the right amount of exfoliating texture when rubbing the bar over my skin. My hands are left feeling quite soft and smell wonderful for much longer than they would with store-bought liquid soaps. A lot of soaps are over-drying, but this one leaves my hands feeling soft rather than dry, my guess is that it's due to the shea butter formula.

I'm very pleased, with these soaps. I've stored them in the drawers of my dresser and my towel closet until I'm ready to use them at the sink because the fragrance is so powerful they make for a great drawer sachet too!

features: ['A must-have makeup tool for your daily beauty care routine', 'High-quality MATERIAL - can be used for personal and professional use', 'Handy product and can be very useful when traveling', 'Each packet contains 6 pieces', 'Quantity: 6 Count']

review: These makeup sponges make me angry.  I used one sponge one time to apply foundation, and it is just waaaay too thin and not dense enough to be effective at all.  You get liquid foundation all over your fingers and under your nails.  And what's with Cala marketing these as a "travel pack"?!  Since when are makeup sponges the problem when deciding what to pack on a trip or put in your carry makeup bag?  You don't need six useless tiny ones.  You need one decent one that fits in your hand and doesn't smoosh down to nothing when you dab it on your skin.  These are so bad, I didn't even use the remaining five - I threw the whole lot in the garbage.  I'll never buy another Cala product again.  So sick of wasting money on poorly designed cosmetic products.  Stay away from this brand, Ladies!  My last pack was great, but unfortunately I have no idea what brand they were.  And I found them in the grocery store for less.

Product Title: LHomme After Shave Balm - 100ml/3.4oz
features: ['100ml/3.4oz', "L'Homme"]
details: {"Brand": "Yves Saint Laurent", "Item Form": "Balm", "Item Volume": "100 Milliliters", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Style": "Modern", "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Language": "English, English, English, English", "Product Dimensions": "3.94 x 4.33 x 4.72 inches; 1.06 Ounces", "Item model number": "3365440339842", "Batteries": "1 Lithium Ion batteries required.", "Manufacturer": "Yves Saint Laurent"}
review:
It has this not quite oily, not quite greasy feel, but thick and slippery enough that it just glides right onto your skin. A much needed lubricant after a close shave. It dries without residues or greasy feelings too and it smells very nice, my wife loves it and says she prefers this scent to my normal cologne. I may have to pony up the dough to buy this stuff in cologne too, but with the price that I have to pay for it, Im glad I only have to buy it twice a year. You really only use like a pea sized dab, where as I had to use 2-3 times as much with my previous aftershave, a gillete lotion. I'll definitely conintue buying this for the rest of my life unless I find something better (or cheaper).

As a side note, I needed to sign for this when the mailman came, which makes me wonder, what ingredients are in here that I need to be 18 or older to use it? If I ever find out, I'll update this review. But after reading the back of it nothing jumped out at me. I work in the flavors and fragrances industry, i.e. I make lotions and creams and things of that nature and I didnt recognize any of the chemicals as something on any of my watch lists.

I use this product for medications and its awesome. I love the interior pockets and the two removable (snap in) zip punches. I can hold 4-6 medication bottles in one zip pouch and then i even keep expensive make up and other things in it too because the walls of the bag are lined with pockets and holders. Its so great. (If you have meds that need to be refridgerated like insulin I've put it in the fridge just fine and have put ice packs in the built in pockets! The brush holders also work very well for holding insulin syringes during travel. There is even a plastic see thru built in pocket where you can pretty safefully store discarded lancets, syringes, etc until ur home or near a proper disposal outlet).

details: {"Brand": "SMPL objects", "Material": "Polyester", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Pattern": "Marble", "Number of Items": "1", "Package Dimensions": "9.21 x 6.97 x 0.67 inches; 0.63 Ounces", "Manufacturer": "SMPL Objects", "Country of Origin": "China"}
review:
So, I just got my shower cap. I’m floored by its PRETTINESS! I haven’t used it in the shower yet, either, but had to come on here to say how awesome it is. I got the “tropical” one, and at first I was upset because I’d gotten it because it said “adjustable”, yet I couldn’t figure out how to adjust it. Turns out, it’s really simple-just untie the bow, then tie it tighter if needed. However, mine needs no adjustment, as far as I can tell. I’d been using plastic shower caps from hotels- you know, disposable? Well, I got a hole in my last one, so it dawned on me- there must exist a reusable shower cap. *duh!* 🤯 So, I went and spent $20.00 on this baby. I am already in love, first thing I did was plop it on my head and it fit PERFECTLY. I then showed my husband, and he, too, plopped it on his head. 😂 I took a pic of him w/ it on, he looks gorgeous. 😉 If this cap can make him look gorgeous, I can imagine what it will do for me lol! So, I thought I’d die spending $20.00 on a shower cap, and here I am considering buying the microfiber towel to match! My hair falls all the way to my HIPS, and takes FOREVER to dry… ok, I’ve got life to live so gotta run, I’ll be back tonight to give you The Update: Post-Shower thoughts!
Have a good one!

Post-Shower Thoughts: WELL! Hair stayed dry, turban in place- this cap is FANTASTIC!!!!!!
If you’re on the fence? TAKE THE PLUNGE!!!
*So* worth it.
👳

My dryer is a Babyliss Pro Portofino Titanium (I hope those are all the right words in the right order) and I couldn't find any reviews anywhere from people who were trying this combo. It works a lot better than my ghetto rubberbands-and-tape trick, no air is escaping from anywhere, so it's all actually going out of the diffuser.
Also, the creator sends a card with your name in it, and she actually spelled mine correctly. This is what convinced me to leave the review, not gonna lie. I know you're thinking, surely the name was right in front of her, but bruva...the misspellings in my life have been nuts.

details: {"Color": "12pcs Sage Green", "Material": "Satin", "Item Form": "Scrunchie", "Brand": "Loanzeg", "Hair Type": "Sage", "Package Dimensions": "7.64 x 5.39 x 4.17 inches; 1.01 Pounds"}
review:
I love these, these are so cute and would be great for a photo-op. They are great items to put into gift bags for your bridesmaids.

I think that these would be so great during the summer, and amazing if someone was having a beach wedding!
(Also, if you are having a girls weekend Bachelorette party, these would also be a great gift for those girls of yours, you all can wear them and match!!!! And then you can have the scrunchies for your wedding!!!)

I can see many opportunities for you and your girls to use these.

A little touch like this, can be fun and I love the heart glasses because they are so cute, but I also love the touch of humor on the scrunchies. The bridal party would love the fact that it says, "to have and to hold your hair back". It makes me smile, every time I read that! It adds abit a humor to it.

These scrunchies are extremely comfortable, my daughter usually hates scrunchies, they usually fall out of her hair easily but she seems to love these. As for the sunglasses, my daughter didn't care to much for it, she said it doesn't sit on her nose correctly but it seemed to look good on her. I actually love the sunglasses. It adds a special touch that we needed.

I would recommend these for a wedding on the beach or in the summer, or if you expect it to be a bright sunny day!

I would also recommend these as items to put into bridesmaids gift bags.

The quality seems to be exactly what I had expected and I am quite pleased.

I would like to note: You may not want go wear the sun glasses all day, but for a few hours here and there, it is quite cute and stylish.

These sun glasses and hair bows would also help coordinate your bridal party, without braking the bank. Little touches like this, really does make a difference.

(These are to be used for wedding next summer.)

review:
This OxygenCeuticals Eye Perfection Duo is the PERFECT COMBINATION! It comes with 1.18fl.oz of Contour Firming Eye Cream and 0.5fl.oz of Age-Defying Eye Serum. It also included sample packets of some of their other products.

details: {"Material": "Stainless Steel", "Brand": "OSRSR", "Water Resistance Level": "Not Water Resistant", "Package Dimensions": "7.91 x 5.63 x 2.24 inches; 11.68 Ounces", "Item model number": "OSRSR021", "UPC": "726324604273", "Manufacturer": "OSRSR"}
review:
These are the first set of cryosticks I’ve ever used and, overall, I think the idea is as great one. The rejuvenating feeling of icy coldness can’t be beat, especially as a way to combat redness\swelling from allergies. These are very smooth and slide across the skin without any issues. I also appreciate that it’s a set of 2, since I keep them in the freezer when not in use and can easily switch between them.

Now for the reason I give these 3 stars: they are terribly balanced and have teeny, tiny handles. The globe part that contains the liquid is sort of heavy and very difficult to manage. After a few minutes of struggling, my fingers and thumb are sore from having to holding on so tightly to a stem that is less in circumference than a pen.

It’s a really silly and short-sighted weakness in an otherwise nice item.

review:
I got this to help me attach my Black Orchid Diffuser to my Babyliss Portofino Dryer. It works great, but it will eventually fall off if I have to dry for a long time - it gets loose with the heat. It doesn’t fall off every time, but I make sure it is secure before drying. It takes forever to dry my hair, so I need to check it occasionally to make sure it is still secure. The diffuser does not stay put at all without this attachment, so definitely need it!

UPDATE: I received a message from Val, the inventor of SnozzlePro - she gave me a tip that helped a lot. I had the nozzle upside down. When I turned it around the way she said to put it, it fit better and did not come off! Changed to 5 stars! Thanks Val!

review: This is a nice athletic headband/ear warmer. The black looks nice and the fabric is smooth and soft to touch, not at all irritating on the skin or face. It’s not very thick…So definitely more of an athletic style versus a cold-weather essentials style. I am able to wear it with my hair pulled back in a ponytail or with my hair down, and it definitely does a good job of keeping my ears sealed in from the wind and cold while outdoors walking my dog. I will say though that I have a pretty medium-sized head for a female, and while it fits me ok, I wouldn’t want it much tighter, so those with known larger heads may want to beware of a potentially tight fit.

review:
I needed a long handle for a back brush with much stiffer bristles that would really SCRIB my back.

This brush feels more like a soft hand sliding smoothly down your back rather than scrubbing it.

So I threw the brush away and jammed the handle into an Eppco HU1310101 Heavy Duty Two Sided Hand & Nail Brush and I'm happy. It has a smaller surface but the bristles actually scrub your skin.

More expensive than I'd like, but it works for me.

details: {"Package Dimensions": "3.9 x 3.6 x 0.9 inches; 1.59 Ounces", "UPC": "681381659829"}
review: Compared to OEM pricing these are a bargain. I was apprehensive about the low price compared to Philips Norelco replacement heads. However, these are of good quality and I recommend that you try them. I followed the guidelines about applying a small drop of baby oil (I used mineral oil) on each head. Just run the shaver for a minute before shaving the first time. This seems to make them work smooth and they give a very comfortable shave. I am glad I took a chance on them as they have given my old shaver new life. I'll use these until the rechargeable battery fails to hold a charge.

Product Title: YanJie Velvet Stretched Button Headband Holder for Nurse Mask Women/Girls/Men 6 Package, Leopard Black Gray Velvet ,Protect your Ear Headband 20inch (Leopard)
details: {"Color": "Gray", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Material": "Velvet", "Fabric Type": "Velvet", "Number of Items": "6", "Package Dimensions": "9.13 x 6.34 x 1.46 inches; 4.59 Ounces", "UPC": "788381037319"}
review:
These headbands are completely necessary for me to live my life these days. I tried other masks extenders but nothing either stayed put, was comfortable, or actually helped with my mask. I have a few different types of mask headbands now - as I wear one every time I leave my house.

These particular ones are pretty nice! If you have a problem with slicker material ones slipping out of your hair - THESE will stay put due to the velour grip on your head. They are not too tight either - some bands I tried squish your brain... The buttons are also the NICEST buttons I have seen on a mask headband like ever. The ONLY flaw with the pretty and matching buttons that are sort of concave are that because of their pretty design once you put your mask strap on them they sort of lift up and away from the band itself (because of their concaveness) - so sort of stick out a bit. So the pretty buttons can be a flaw. But they work just fine - and it is probably me being anal.

The buttons are also at a decent placement. I wish they were the slightest bit lower, though - as that works best for me. As they are now they are still good - any higher and they would be pulling your nose up by your mask. The colors (other than the wilder animal print) are muted enough to easily wear to the office as well. A headband is literally part of my everyday office wear now. Glad I can add these to my collection of bands! If you found my review helpful, why not click the "Helpful" button. Thanks! : )

review:
I really wanted these to work for me. I’m so disappointed because I purchased the two pack so that I could give one to my mom for her birthday and keep one for myself (it was a much better deal to get the two pack instead of just the single). I used it once and I was not impressed at all. It’s very cute and the perfect shade of light pink. But functionality was not there. I put my china glaze nail polish in it and put it on my middle and ring fingers of my left hand and started to paint my toe nails. Nothing bad happened but it really wasn’t better than just setting the bottle on the table. So I’m giving it 3 stars for the cute factor, and the fact that it held the polish fine. I read that if your polish bottle doesn’t fit just lift one or more of the petals until it fits.

Product Title: Pure Body Naturals Micellar Cleansing Water, All-in-1 Cleanser & Makeup Remover, 8 Fl. Oz.
details: {"Item Form": "Liquid", "Skin Type": "All", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Unit Count": "8.0 Fl Oz", "Item Package Quantity": "1", "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Package Dimensions": "4.5 x 0.8 x 0.1 inches; 11.2 Ounces", "UPC": "712038210213"}
review: So far so good. I have acne prone skin, and I broke out from the Garnier Micellar water. I decided to try this one because Pure Body Naturals has consistently good products. I've been using strictly as a toner. Because I have acne prone skin, I cannot use this as a makeup remover, cleaner alone. I wash my face, and then use this as a toner, I also do not use this as an eye makeup remover, in general, I find most eye makeup removers to be very harsh, burning around the eyes. I keep eye makeup remover simple. Vaseline, or just Dove soap. The smell of this is amazing, it's clear that this is legit lavender essential oil. Knowing that, I don't think I'd put it around my eyes either. I haven't broken out from this micellar water at all so I will continue use. The only thing I found odd around this bottle is that it clearly says "Lavender Cleanser" but the instructions and writing on the back calls it "Blueberry" water. What? Lol.

Product Title: Philips Norelco T970 Accu-Vac Beard and Moustache Trimmer
features: ['Stainless Steel Self Sharpening Blades offer lifetime precision cutting', 'Patented zoom lock locks into 9 different settings for your desired beard length', 'Rechargeable, Cord / Cordless for use with our without a cord.', '1 hour charge time, battery level indicator', '60 Day Money Back Guarantee']
details: {"Package Dimensions": "9.7 x 6 x 4.6 inches; 1.58 Pounds", "Item model number": "T970", "UPC": "075020189707", "Manufacturer": "Philips Norelco"}
review:
As an owner of the previous model without the vacuum, I was looking forward to this new purchase. Bah. This item is heavier, noisier and more inconvenient than its predecessor. And for practically no gain! This shaver catches maybe 10% of the clipped hair with the rest of it flying all over the sink.

Stay away from this model.

Update: I've owned Norelco trimmers in the past, however based on my experience with this particular model, my next trimmer will NOT be a Norelco. The fan which drives the vaccuum rattles against the plastic housing, making a hideous noice while I'm trimming. The vaccuum action is terrible; hairs don't make it down into the receptacle, causing constant blockage. This in turn, scatters hair all over the place, worse than any conventional non-vac trimmer I've ever owned. (And no, my beard is not especially thick either.) I've finally had it with this model. I'm about to order a new trimmer on Amazon. No, it won't be a Norelco.

review: While the concept of the built in comb is a good one, this design just does not work well and don't count on the vacuum catching all your clippings because it can only hold about half the volume of a shot glass. I ended throwing mine away and switching back to my old Oster hair clippers with the snap on combs for my head and bought a small rechargeable Waring beard trimmer. The twist dial for the comb length on this unit can be wrong - I gouged my beard/sideburns once with this unit. The comb unit must be removed for frequent cleaning and putting it back on correctly takes a delicate touch. The large size of the unit and comb also makes it verr difficult to trim your moustache close to your nose. Don't waste your money.

details: {"Water Resistance Level": "Water Resistant", "Pattern": "Floral", "Number of Pieces": "15", "Package Dimensions": "8.35 x 5.94 x 0.24 inches; 3.67 Ounces"}
review:
I'd give these tatoos even more stars if I could! I got these for a sci-fi theme murder mystery and they were perfect! So many to choose from for guests to make themselves look alien, pretty, or tough. The matallic makes them really pop. I had people think my braclet was real jewelry and someone else thought it was a real tattoo.

The tattoos went on easily and I was impressed with how long they stayed. I was even able to get one to stick over the top of face paint.

I took the face paint and tattoos over it off that evening. They rubbed off easily with makeup remover. A tattoo on my bare cheek lasted until the next evening when I accidentally rubbed part of it off while scratching my cheek. One on my neck lasted a couple more days, one on the back of my hand about four days, and one around my wrist lasted almost a full week with only a little fading and one small edge rubbed away. (Note, they can be removed immediately if you don't want them that long.)

I'm very pleased with the quality, quantity, and price of these. We have lots left and I look forward to using them again.

review:
These are by far the best chrome powders I have tried. I have tried 5 other brands and none came close to how shiny there powders did. All the colors are beautiful . I love that they put instruction that are pretty detailed other sellers just ship the powders and don't tell you anything so that's nice for beginners. For the price it isn't bad but I feel that they should tell us which color is to what number . On the bottom there's a sticker going up to 12 they should have a color graph saying which is which it was a pain to use all the test nails they provide to figure out and wasted a good amount of gel top coat that's the only thing I would add. Other than that I would recommend getting these for sure . For first timers you need a non wipe top coat my favorites are from" onedor " and "pretty diva" make sure it says no wipe. I don't use black gel polish for base regular black nail polish works as you can see in my photo that's the way I did it
I hope this helps have a great day! :)

details: {"Brand": "Osensia", "Item Form": "Cream", "Material Feature": "Sulfate Free", "Hair Type": "Oily, Dry, Curly, Normal", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Package Dimensions": "4.02 x 3.39 x 2.8 inches; 1.05 Pounds", "UPC": "712038284344", "Manufacturer": "Osensia"}
review: I love this conditioner but not for the reasons most noted in the reviews. My hair is extremely fine, loose curls, moderately thick and easily tangles.Over time, my hair had become so severely matted that I could not run a comb or a brush through it.  I used the TRESemmé conditioner and even though my hair was smooth and soft, I could not untangle the mess. Pulling on my hair to separate the tangles was painful so I started cutting out the masses of hair instead. Thankfully, I remembered purchasing the Argan Oil Mask and decided to give it a try. I covered the tangles for over the 30 minutes with the conditioner, rinsed and was able to untangle my hair with my fingers. With the newly conditioned hair, I could separate the tangles without pain. Is my hair unusually soft with this conditioner? No, but it sure strengthened my hair and it seems so thick now!  This is a plus because prior to using this conditioner, I had cut out quite a number of tangles leaving all different lengths. I am extremely happy with not having to cut off an additional third of my hair!

review:
This is my first time buying real human hair but I know the stats and I did my research beforehand. If you are a first time buyer like me you won’t be disappointed with this company. I got my hair and was skeptical about it so I did the pull test and burn test. They both checked out and the hair has double wefts. I forgot to take a before picture but the hair looks just like the company demonstration. I washed the hair first with a co-wash cleanser and let it dry overnight. It doesn’t tangle bad or shed much. It curls well naturally or with heat. The middle picture was natural curls using twist with curling cream and Carol’s daughter mousse. The others were with a 1” curling wand on 330 degrees and coconut oil and Tresseme heat tamer spray. Coconut oil works excellent for this hair by the way. I recently washed my hair with it still on my head with sulfate free shampoo and conditioner. It’s hard to dry my hair underneath with a blow dryer but I still protect the weave like my own hair or better because it is very delicate. This hair is so soft and manageable I wish it were my own and I feel like this is how my hair should be. The hair is darker than I thought but I got used to it. It’s like a dark dark brown. I glad I found real human hair for a low price and 16, 18 and 20” was longer than I thought. I got a closure also because I am 10 weeks into needing a relaxer. The closure is ok but I wanted a more natural look but I still got the closure to look real. I’m in absolute aw of this hair. This is a real honest review and trust me, you won’t regret this purchase.

details: {"Manufacturer": "HANASCAR"}
review:
For this price you get 6 individually sealed containers of remover pads. They each contain 38 thin fabric-like removal pads that are soaked in the non-acetone remover. The containers screw open and don't seem to dry out easily. The remover contains isopropyl myristate, propylene carbonate, fragrance, and water. These are ideal for anyone who doesn't like the smell of acetone since they just smell flowery. They smell wonderful, I'm someone who doesn't like many scented things, but they are all very soft pretty scents that I love.

The pads remove polish more slowly than most acetone-based nail polish removers and require a bit of scrubbing. To remove a bright red (read-as nail polish that stains) manicure I use 3-4 sheets (more if there is glitter in the polish). They do leave your nails and hands a bit greasy feeling (which means they moisturize your nails rather than drying them out like acetone) so you should always wash your hands thoroughly after using the remover pads. Overall, great product and I will buy it again (once these run out, they last forever!)

Product Title: Philips Norelco T970 Accu-Vac Beard and Moustache Trimmer
features: ['Stainless Steel Self Sharpening Blades offer lifetime precision cutting', 'Patented zoom lock locks into 9 different settings for your desired beard length', 'Rechargeable, Cord / Cordless for use with our without a cord.', '1 hour charge time, battery level indicator', '60 Day Money Back Guarantee']
details: {"Package Dimensions": "9.7 x 6 x 4.6 inches; 1.58 Pounds", "Item model number": "T970", "UPC": "075020189707", "Manufacturer": "Philips Norelco"}
review:
This popped up in my gold box, and I decided to give it a whirl since the idea of trimming my beard with no mess had a lot of appeal. The vacuum does half work. Unfortunately, catching half the mess won't change the need for clean-up--there's less to clean, but you'll still need to do it. So my main recommendation is that you shouldn't let the vacuum "feature" be your reason for buying this. If anything, it's a slight negative, because the opening for the vacuum gets in the way when you are doing edge trimming without the attachment.
The next down-side is the "memory" rechargeable batteries. Basically, unless you let the batteries completely discharge before recharging, they will hold less and less charge each time. This is mentioned in the folded up piece of paper that passes for a manual--you will want to read through that. Which leads me to my final gripe: That piece of paper is extremely poorly done--diagrams with no explaination, unclear instructions, etc. So you do have to read it, but you're going to spend some time trying to puzzle it out before you actually figure it out.
For all my complaining, the trimmer isn't completely without merit. It does do a decent job of trimming my beard, which is of course the main point of the thing. I also didn't have any real noise complaints, which seems to be an issue for other reviewers.
On balance though, my main recommendation would be don't pay for the vacuum, because you won't be getting what you paid for.

details: {"Brand": "Elice", "Color": "Blue,Green,White,Pink,Silver,Purple", "Material": "Metal, Crystal", "Unit Count": "12.00 Count", "Number of Pieces": "12", "UPC": "793002442779"}
review: I bought these to pull my bangs out of my hair.  I have fine, straight hair, and nothing tends to stay there except tiny elastics and you can't get those out without losing hair.  I love these!!  They have been perfect.  Now my granddaughters are asking to use them to pull their bangs out of their hair.  My problem was finding a barrette small enough.  I'd prefer a bit of bling without the dragonfly or perhaps a butterfly, but thankfully, I do like dragonflies.  I'm just 53 so straight would be better.  Anyway, no real complaints. Been using ONE of them for weeks.  No problem.  The grandkids are using the others, losing them randomly.  I'll wind up having to buy more.  It was great and I am glad I did.  It hold straight fine hair of my 5-year-old granddaughters, my 3-year-old granddaughters, and this grandma's bangs.  My 8-year-old granddaughter is using them too, but her hair is so thick you could use anything!  We other 3 are the fine thin-haired people, and they are awesome!

features: ['Perfect for a large makeup collection', 'Built-in 14 brush holder in lid with cover; Customize space with 5 adjustable dividers', 'Convenient handle for easy carrying; Sturdy key lock', 'Removable, divided, upper tray for simple access to lower compartment', 'Hard-sided construction prevents items from being crushed']
details: {"Product Dimensions": "9.75 x 9.13 x 15.38 inches; 2.8 Pounds", "Item model number": "VZ03755", "UPC": "826030037553", "Manufacturer": "Ideastream Consumer Products, LLC"}
review:
I’m really liking this case.

I got the “every day” case. I’d like if it had some more pockets, but the snap-in makeup cases are more handy than I expected. It’s easy to just remove one of the bags and then close and secure the case again if you want. The slots for storing makeup brushes are handy, too.

It was easy to set my own security code, and it’s pretty easy to lock and unlock. This isn’t a high-security solution, since someone could cut the case open if they wanted to, but it IS a great solution if you want to ensure some privacy or make it impossible for someone to be stealthy about stealing small items. Example: if you have roommates or family members who might want to sneak some of your medication, storing it locked in this case would make it impossible for them to do so without leaving obvious evidence of the theft.

Please measure and confirm your hair dryer nozzle diameter BEFORE purchase.', 'FITS XTAVA BLACK ORCHID HAIR DIFFUSER: SnozzlePro’s super-tight fit on the Xtava Black Orchid Hair Diffuser is designed to grip and support the added weight of this short nozzle hair diffuser.', "PREVENTS CONCENTRATOR NOZZLE POP-OFFS: SnozzlePro's patented design keeps hair dryer concentrator nozzles securely attached for a perfect fit and protects hands from heat.", 'HOW TO USE - SnozzlePro comes with detailed HOW-TO-USE instructions. DYSON HAIR DRYER USERS: Insert the Dyson "Smoothing" nozzle ONLY HALFWAY into the larger end of the SnozzlePro. (Over-inserting the nozzle will cause the diffuser to detach.)']
details: {"Product Dimensions": "2.5 x 2.5 x 2.5 inches; 2.08 Ounces", "Item model number": "SP-100", "UPC": "860002276502", "Manufacturer": "Snozzle Pro"}
review: This does work. I invested in a nicer hair dryer (so worth it, why did I take decades to do this) but could not imagine living without my orchid diffuser. After trying a lot of things I found this. It does work, it stays on. It's probably a little expensive for what it is but I'm actually impressed someone decided to make some money off of the popularity of these diffusers and solve a problem thousands of us have. My real question is for the folks who make those diffusers--why on earth not make them with a longer attachment or a stretchy attachment so they fit more dryers? Lost opportunity. Regardless, glad someone took the initiative to create this product and I'm impressed and surprised it works so well.

details: {"Brand": "Maybelline New York", "Color": "Rebel red", "Skin Type": "All", "Item Form": "Stick", "Finish Type": "Matte", "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Product Dimensions": "0.79 x 0.71 x 3.66 inches; 0.28 Ounces", "Item model number": "3600531322144", "UPC": "615908417685 756567760030"}
review: I love a great matte lip and add this gorgeous shade of red and you’d think it would be a home run. No No No in my Destiny’s Child voice. Maybelline color sensational Vivid Matte liquid lipstick left me scratching my head,the first thing I noticed was a strong fragrance almost like I’d sprayed perfume on my lips,the second thing I noticed was the matte was not a true matte it was a little glossy even after leaving it on a while. I also noticed some stinging I’m assuming it was due to the crazy amount of fragrance added to this product. This particular shade of red looks very similar to a Stila lip cream that I’m in love with which excited me, but once I applied Maybelline Vivid Matte I found this red was not at all flattering to my brown skin. And lastly this left me #afraid to try any new Maybelline lip products.

Product Title: Pure Body Naturals Micellar Cleansing Water, All-in-1 Cleanser & Makeup Remover, 8 Fl. Oz.
details: {"Item Form": "Liquid", "Skin Type": "All", "Age Range (Description)": "Adult", "Unit Count": "8.0 Fl Oz", "Item Package Quantity": "1", "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Package Dimensions": "4.5 x 0.8 x 0.1 inches; 11.2 Ounces", "UPC": "712038210213"}
review:
I absolutely love this cleansing water. I have never tried cleansing water before, but I was curious if it was different than a cleansing lotion. I use an acne lotion, but if I switch lotions my acne returns. That lotion, however, does a horrible job removing my make-up, especially my eye make-up. So I put this cleansing water on a cotton pad, and it took very little to quickly and easily remove my eye make-up. I now use it every night and consider now a permanent part of my night-time beauty routine. There bottle does come with a top (t keep it from spilling when traveling), and then a pump for every day use.

*note: it says lavender, but I don't notice any fragrance which is good, I don't like lavender)
