DYSON HAIR DRYER USERS: Insert the Dyson "Smoothing" nozzle ONLY HALFWAY into the larger end of the SnozzlePro. (Over-inserting the nozzle will cause the diffuser to detach.)']
details: {"Product Dimensions": "2.5 x 2.5 x 2.5 inches; 2.08 Ounces", "Item model number": "SP-100", "UPC": "860002276502", "Manufacturer": "Snozzle Pro"}
review:
I really wanted to love this. I have a Dyson dryer, which I live, but I had an orchid diffuser in the past that was AMAZING. However, there’s only one dryer an orchid diffuser fits on and i went through 2 of them in a year (the first one just died and the second one started SPARKING IN MY HAIR!). I saw videos on how the SnozzlePro could connect an orchid to a dyson and I was all in. It works. It does connect the two, but it is so heavy that the magnetic connection between the attachment you put the SnozzlePro on with the orchid diffuser cannot stay connected to the dryer. I spent the whole time trying to hold the attachment to the dryer, and when I couldn’t it was pop off and blow fast hair into my damp curls which creates a ton of frizz.

I think I can still dig it to work, and it does what it says: creates a connection point for attachments, but it isn’t perfect and I don’t know if a tube of silicone is worth the price.

details: {"Brand": "Anterogen", "Item Form": "Sheet, Gel", "Product Benefits": "Hydrating, Exfoliating, Fine Lines Treatment, Nourishing, Anti Aging, Firming", "Scent": "Unscented", "Skin Type": "acne prone", "Product Dimensions": "7.28 x 5.91 x 0.79 inches; 5.57 Ounces"}
review:
I really loved this mask!! It is one of the only wrinkle products that you can see a notice difference after! The only reason why I am giving it 4 stars is because it states that there are two masks in each one and there isn’t, it’s two halves to one mask, the bottom
And the top. With that being said you get three masks total, each order comes with three. But the masks themselves really adhere to the skin and it truly seems to fill in the lines, it’s really quite amazing actually! it feels so good on your skin! I recommend putting masks in fridge, they actually recommend it too. I also put the empty pack in the fridge and then use the rest of the serum for a few days until it’s gone! But it’s def worth it! I will be buying again! For people who are afraid to try it you should give it a shot! I’ve used a lot of products that promise a lot
Of things and this is one that stands up to those promises! If your looking to erase fine lines or even acne scars I strongly recommend it!

The worst part about these massage tools is that the silicon tips (handles) should be longer so that not only can you hold them easier but also so that your hands don't freeze while using the massager.
A convenient carry case/freezer case is included.
Highly recommend!

Product Title: U Tip Dark Golden Blonde Highlight Platinum Blonde Fusion Extensions Human Hair 14inch 50g 1g/s
details: {"Brand": "Sunny Hair", "Material": "Human Hair", "Extension Length": "14 Inches", "Hair Type": "Straight", "Installation Type": "Fusion", "Is Discontinued By Manufacturer": "No", "Product Dimensions": "18 x 1 x 1 inches; 1.76 Ounces", "UPC": "711301068834"}
review:
My once beautiful long hair is finally growing back in from chemotherapy for breast cancer. I had had it bonded by my hair salon about 6 months ago with Cinderella bonds that shed like a cat almost immediately and had hair that was split and damaged before I ever even washed it.

I took a chance on ordering 2-18 inch packs of #613 and 2-16 inch packs of #613 of Sunny hair. The hair looked beautiful and was a perfect match for my own color, but there is no way of telling until it's been washed, conditioned and blown out over a few weeks to really know how it will hold up.

My stylist, who specializes in hot fusion bonds, put in 1 pack of the 18 inch Sunny hair (50 U tips) and one pack of Cinderella hair (25 U tips) 5 days ago. I have very fine hair and a tiny head, so more would not have been possible (this amount also equals a full head of hair for me). We are experimenting to see which hair holds up better.

After one wash, conditioning and blow dry yesterday, the high priced Cinderella hair was tangling in the middle, while the Sunny hair stayed tangle-fee, but did shed quite a bit. The Sunny hair has more weight to it than the much more expensive hair though and combed out better.

One star off for how huge the actual keratin U-tip are and the shedding. My stylist tried to cut some of the tip off with great difficulty. This is an FYI for those with fine hair or those who want to be able to pull it back without the bond showing (the more expensive type has much smaller Keratin u-tips).

I will update this review after 4 weeks in, but for now, I'd like to thank other reviewers for their input as it helped me choose Sunny hair. You were all correct in saying the hair is thicker than most online hair, even though each strand is a bit different in strand width, health and quality. As the industry is unregulated, it's hard to know what you're getting and with blonde hair, just how much processing went into coloring the hair (causing damage).

If my Sunny hair holds up well, my stylist, who does at least 10 hot fusion bondings per month on clients, will be ordering directly from Sunny hair instead of the company that charges $125-$150 per pack. We are both hoping this is the case.

I hope others will try this brand and leave reviews on their experiences. Also, if this is your first time with bonds, please remember on length that it's not going from the top of your head. The lower layers will fall much longer - I'm 5'7 with a long neck and the 18 inch lower tiers fall just a few inches above my waist.

UPDATE: please don't buy this hair if you value your natural hair.
It's impossible to remove the bonds without breaking your own hair.
It breaks, frizzes, knots up like crazy if in a warm climate.
I loved those first packs until summertime. Absolutely awful in heat and humidity. I couldn't get a brush through the hair. It would just snap off. The knots were horrific. I had my hairdresser try to remove and this is more like crazy glue on the bond than keratin.

review:
This device has serious functional and aesthetic flaws. On a functional level, the vacuum is virtually useless so that at least 2/3 of the hair winds up on the counter or in the sink. I could have stayed with my non-vacuum trimmer! Also, the blades clog and everything comes apart to clean with a flimsy, I hope I don't break this, kind of plasticity.

On an aesthetic level, this is very noisy and the noise is extremely unpleasant, sort of a sick screeching sound that I do not associate with quality. As soon as I turn it on, I want to turn it off as soon as possible. This just does not feel like a quality product. It is within a hair of it being worth the trouble to return it.

details: {"Material": "Acrylic", "Brand": "Fashion Zone", "Finish Type": "Glossy", "Item Form": "Gel", "Package Dimensions": "8.6 x 6.9 x 3.8 inches; 1.55 Pounds", "UPC": "603004594225"}
review: It took longer to dry then it probably should, but what I found out is that, yes, it is sticky between coats. And that made me very nervous. All I could think was how am I going to get this sticky , gunky stuff off of my nails. But I just kept pushing forward and putting on the next step and low and behold the top coat seem to do the trick. I put it on and then dried them for 120 seconds and it was done. I did it one more time just to be sure because I found it hard to believe that all the coats of sticky gunky suddenly went away. And it worked. Now I just wish I had a steady hand because I'm guessing getting the little bits of gel polish off my skin could be a party. That's my own fault.

features: ['Perfect for a large makeup collection', 'Built-in 14 brush holder in lid with cover; Customize space with 5 adjustable dividers', 'Convenient handle for easy carrying; Sturdy key lock', 'Removable, divided, upper tray for simple access to lower compartment', 'Hard-sided construction prevents items from being crushed']

review:
I was getting sick of finding that my feminine products supply was running low because other people at work were taking from my bag - but I also didn't want to have to carry a bag with me to the bathroom every time I need to go while on my period. I decided to buy two of these so that I could store one in each of our work bathrooms (so that I don't have to wait for the "specific bathroom" that has all my supplies - now both do!).

Each bag has enough room for storage for every feminine product possible - I fit 4 extra thick pads, a dozen tampons, about 20 liners and at least a dozen "slim" pads. It's pretty full, but there is still more room to spare - I just preferred to not have it bulging, for easier zip/close. And that's what fits in just ONE bag! Product Title: Vaultz Locking Makeup Artist Case, Black White Stripe (VZ03755)
features: ['Perfect for a large makeup collection', 'Built-in 14 brush holder in lid with cover; Customize space with 5 adjustable dividers', 'Convenient handle for easy carrying; Sturdy key lock', 'Removable, divided, upper tray for simple access to lower compartment', 'Hard-sided construction prevents items from being crushed']
details: {"Product Dimensions": "9.75 x 9.13 x 15.38 inches; 2.8 Pounds", "Item model number": "VZ03755", "UPC": "826030037553", "Manufacturer": "Ideastream Consumer Products, LLC"}
review:
This case is beautiful on the outside, but has given me nothing but problems. Sometimes the box will lock, and sometimes it won't. Sometimes it will unlock on the first try, and sometimes it will unlock on the 10th try. Sometimes the key keeps spinning, and spinning...and spinning. As you can gather, the lock mechanism and key on this case isn't great, so I wouldn't trust this as an actual "lock box." I would definitely look for something that utilizes a better made lock and key.

The lid also has a very hard time staying open on its own. Not only that, but the material on the inside is very cheap. While I love the color and the compartments on the top for holding things like eyeliner pencils (or regular pencils) and other flat items, I expected the quality to be a bit better.

I have another Vaultz case that I bought 2.5 years ago that is very durable and reliable when it comes to the lock, so I expected this to be better.

Maybe, just maybe, i received a defective case.
